coordination.} 21. e5 Qd7 22. Nb4 Bxe5 23. Bxe5 Rxe5 24. Qxd7 Bxd7 25. Rd2 Be6
$11 {The endgame is completely equal.}) 17... Qc5 $1 {[%csl Rd4][%cal Gc5g1] I
think objectively is the best option.} ({Also possible is:} 17... Qf6 18. Ne2
bxc6 19. Bxc4 dxc4 20. Rc2 $1 ({Of course not} 20. Rxc4 $2 {in view of} Ba6 $17
{[%csl Rc4,Re2,Rf4][%cal Ga6e2]}) 20... Ba6 21. Bd2 $1 {A very nice manouvre.}
Rad8 22. Qc1 $14 {[%cal Gd2c3] For sure White keeps small plus.}) 18. Be3 $1 {
The whole point of 17.Rc1. The next couple of moves is very forced.} Nxe3 19.
Rxc5 Nxd1 20. Rxd1 bxc6 ({of course not} 20... dxe4 $2 21. c7 $18 {[%csl Gc7]})
21. Ba4 {[%cal Ga4c6] White has some option here, but with accurate moves,
Black is holding everywhere.} (21. exd5 $2 {This is the whole point for Black
that here the move} Re1+ $1 {[%csl Rc5,Rd4][%cal Gg7d4] Just wins.}) (21. Rxc6
{Another reasonable option.} dxe4 22. Rc7 {[%csl Rf7][%cal Gb3f7]} Rd8 $1 {
[%cal Gd8d1] A very important move.} 23. Rxf7 ({Also equal is:} 23. Nc6 Rxd1+
24. Bxd1 Be6 25. fxe4 Bxb2 $11) 23... Kh8 24. Nb5 Rxd1+ 25. Bxd1 Rb8 $11 {
[%csl Rb2][%cal Gb8b2] Black's bishops compensate the pawn down.}) (21. Nxc6
dxe4 22. Nd8 {[%csl Rf7][%cal Gb3f7,Gd8f7] Looks nice,but after:} (22. fxe4
Bxb2) 22... Be6 23. Nxe6 fxe6 24. fxe4 Bxb2 $11 {Black can't lose here.}) 21...
Bb7 {The only defence. Here Black has to make a few only moves.} 22. Nxc6 dxe4
23. Na5 {[%csl Rb7,Re8]} Re7 24. Nxb7 Rxb7 25. Bc6 Rc8 {[%csl Rc5][%cal Gc8c5]}
26. Bxb7 Rxc5 27. Rd8+ Bf8 28. fxe4 {[%csl} Rd5 {[%cal Gb7d5] Looks more
logical to cement the bishop on the d5 square.} ({Black will hold very easy
after: Bxe4} 28... h5 $11) {Rc7 It is important to not allow Rd7.} 29. Bxd5 Kg7
{Liberates the bishop. Black is a pawn down, but the opposite-coloured bishops
and the activity on the c-file give Black a nice counterplay. I believe the
endgame is almost completely equal.} 30. Kf1 Be7 {A nice intermediate move.
The point is to bring the rook to the more ugly square a8.} 31. Ra8 Bc5 {
[%cal Gc5b6] Black's idea is Bb6 and to penetrate with the rook via the c-
file.} 32. b3 Bb6 $11 {[%cal Gc7c2]} 33. Bc4 {[%csl Re4] A nice try to close
the file, but after: Re7 White must repeat the moves.} *

